            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EJesus%20described%20the%20devil%20as%20a%20murderer%20from%20the%20beginning%20of%20time%2C%20and%20this%20description%20also%20serves%20to%20illustrate%20the%20life%20of%20King%20Saul.%20When%20an%20evil%20spirit%20came%20upon%20Saul%20to%20possess%20him%2C%20he%20was%20overwhelmed%20with%20thoughts%20of%20envy%20and%20murder%20toward%20David.%20Time%20after%20time%20he%20tried%20to%20destroy%20David%2C%20even%20attempting%20to%20pin%20him%20to%20the%20wall%20with%20a%20spear%20(1%20Samuel%2018%3A10-11).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESatan%20is%20envious%20of%20believers%20because%20they%20have%20replaced%20him%20as%20worshipers%20and%20sons%20of%20God.%20His%20hatred%20for%20humankind%20knows%20no%20bounds.%20He%20always%20seeks%20%22to%20steal%20and%20kill%20and%20destroy%22%20(John%2010%3A10)%2C%20and%20He%20wants%20to%20destroy%20you!%20%20%20%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EJesus%20said%20that%20the%20devil%20is%20a%20liar%20and%20the%20father%20of%20lies.%20Saul%20lied%20to%20David%20and%20told%20him%20he%20wanted%20to%20give%20his%20older%20daughter%20Merab%20in%20marriage%20to%20him.%20In%20fact%2C%20he%20wanted%20David%20killed%20by%20the%20Philistines%20(1%20Samuel%2018%3A17).%20David's%20innocence%2C%20however%2C%20was%20his%20protection.%20The%20Lord%20sent%20the%20Holy%20Spirit%20to%20knock%20to%20the%20ground%20the%20soldiers%20who%20chased%20David.%20Even%20Saul%20himself%20was%20knocked%20to%20the%20ground%20(19%3A23-24).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ELet%20us%20rejoice%20that%20even%20though%20Satan%20attacks%20with%20lies%20and%20murderous%20intents%2C%20the%20Holy%20Spirit%20can%20render%20our%20enemies%20harmless.%20We%20will%20fulfill%20our%20purposes%20in%20God!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
