            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "1Sam.18:5-19:24",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E1%20Samuel%2018%3A5-19%3A24%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_5%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EWhatever%20Saul%20asked%20David%20to%20do%2C%20David%20did%20it%20successfully.%20So%20Saul%20made%20him%20a%20commander%20over%20the%20men%20of%20war%2C%20an%20appointment%20that%20was%20welcomed%20by%20the%20people%20and%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20officers%20alike.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_6%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20the%20victorious%20Israelite%20army%20was%20returning%20home%20after%20David%20had%20killed%20the%20Philistine%2C%20women%20from%20all%20the%20towns%20of%20Israel%20came%20out%20to%20meet%20King%20Saul.%20They%20sang%20and%20danced%20for%20joy%20with%20tambourines%20and%20cymbals.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E18%3A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%20The%20type%20of%20instrument%20represented%20by%20the%20word%20%3Cem%3Ecymbals%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20uncertain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_7%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20was%20their%20song%3A%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet1-sp%22%3E%26%23x201C%3BSaul%20has%20killed%20his%20thousands%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22poet2%22%3Eand%20David%20his%20ten%20thousands!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_8%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-sp%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20made%20Saul%20very%20angry.%20%26%23x201C%3BWhat%26%23x2019%3Bs%20this%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20said.%20%26%23x201C%3BThey%20credit%20David%20with%20ten%20thousands%20and%20me%20with%20only%20thousands.%20Next%20they%26%23x2019%3Bll%20be%20making%20him%20their%20king!%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_9%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20from%20that%20time%20on%20Saul%20kept%20a%20jealous%20eye%20on%20David.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_10%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20very%20next%20day%20a%20tormenting%20spirit%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E18%3A10%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Ean%20evil%20spirit.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20from%20God%20overwhelmed%20Saul%2C%20and%20he%20began%20to%20rave%20in%20his%20house%20like%20a%20madman.%20David%20was%20playing%20the%20harp%2C%20as%20he%20did%20each%20day.%20But%20Saul%20had%20a%20spear%20in%20his%20hand%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_11%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20he%20suddenly%20hurled%20it%20at%20David%2C%20intending%20to%20pin%20him%20to%20the%20wall.%20But%20David%20escaped%20him%20twice.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_12%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3ESaul%20was%20then%20afraid%20of%20David%2C%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20was%20with%20David%20and%20had%20turned%20away%20from%20Saul.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_13%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EFinally%2C%20Saul%20sent%20him%20away%20and%20appointed%20him%20commander%20over%201%2C000%20men%2C%20and%20David%20faithfully%20led%20his%20troops%20into%20battle.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_14%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20continued%20to%20succeed%20in%20everything%20he%20did%2C%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20was%20with%20him.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_15%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Saul%20recognized%20this%2C%20he%20became%20even%20more%20afraid%20of%20him.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_16%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20all%20Israel%20and%20Judah%20loved%20David%20because%20he%20was%20so%20successful%20at%20leading%20his%20troops%20into%20battle.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_17%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%20Marries%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Daughter%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EOne%20day%20Saul%20said%20to%20David%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%20am%20ready%20to%20give%20you%20my%20older%20daughter%2C%20Merab%2C%20as%20your%20wife.%20But%20first%20you%20must%20prove%20yourself%20to%20be%20a%20real%20warrior%20by%20fighting%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20battles.%26%23x201D%3B%20For%20Saul%20thought%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BI%26%23x2019%3Bll%20send%20him%20out%20against%20the%20Philistines%20and%20let%20them%20kill%20him%20rather%20than%20doing%20it%20myself.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_18%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BWho%20am%20I%2C%20and%20what%20is%20my%20family%20in%20Israel%20that%20I%20should%20be%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20son-in-law%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20David%20exclaimed.%20%26%23x201C%3BMy%20father%26%23x2019%3Bs%20family%20is%20nothing!%26%23x201D%3B%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_19%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E18%3A19%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3EBut.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20when%20the%20time%20came%20for%20Saul%20to%20give%20his%20daughter%20Merab%20in%20marriage%20to%20David%2C%20he%20gave%20her%20instead%20to%20Adriel%2C%20a%20man%20from%20Meholah.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_20%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20daughter%20Michal%20had%20fallen%20in%20love%20with%20David%2C%20and%20Saul%20was%20delighted%20when%20he%20heard%20about%20it.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_21%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BHere%26%23x2019%3Bs%20another%20chance%20to%20see%20him%20killed%20by%20the%20Philistines!%26%23x201D%3B%20Saul%20said%20to%20himself.%20But%20to%20David%20he%20said%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BToday%20you%20have%20a%20second%20chance%20to%20become%20my%20son-in-law!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_22%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20Saul%20told%20his%20men%20to%20say%20to%20David%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThe%20king%20really%20likes%20you%2C%20and%20so%20do%20we.%20Why%20don%26%23x2019%3Bt%20you%20accept%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20offer%20and%20become%20his%20son-in-law%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_23%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2223%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E23%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20men%20said%20these%20things%20to%20David%2C%20he%20replied%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BHow%20can%20a%20poor%20man%20from%20a%20humble%20family%20afford%20the%20bride%20price%20for%20the%20daughter%20of%20a%20king%3F%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_24%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2224%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20men%20reported%20this%20back%20to%20the%20king%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_25%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3Ehe%20told%20them%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BTell%20David%20that%20all%20I%20want%20for%20the%20bride%20price%20is%20100%26%23xA0%3BPhilistine%20foreskins!%20Vengeance%20on%20my%20enemies%20is%20all%20I%20really%20want.%26%23x201D%3B%20But%20what%20Saul%20had%20in%20mind%20was%20that%20David%20would%20be%20killed%20in%20the%20fight.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_26%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2226%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E26%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20was%20delighted%20to%20accept%20the%20offer.%20Before%20the%20time%20limit%20expired%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_27%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E27%3C%2Fspan%3Ehe%20and%20his%20men%20went%20out%20and%20killed%20200%26%23xA0%3BPhilistines.%20Then%20David%20fulfilled%20the%20king%26%23x2019%3Bs%20requirement%20by%20presenting%20all%20their%20foreskins%20to%20him.%20So%20Saul%20gave%20his%20daughter%20Michal%20to%20David%20to%20be%20his%20wife.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_28%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E28%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20Saul%20realized%20that%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20was%20with%20David%20and%20how%20much%20his%20daughter%20Michal%20loved%20him%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_29%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E29%3C%2Fspan%3ESaul%20became%20even%20more%20afraid%20of%20him%2C%20and%20he%20remained%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20enemy%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20life.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_18_30%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2218%22%20vn%3D%2230%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E30%3C%2Fspan%3EEvery%20time%20the%20commanders%20of%20the%20Philistines%20attacked%2C%20David%20was%20more%20successful%20against%20them%20than%20all%20the%20rest%20of%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20officers.%20So%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20name%20became%20very%20famous.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_19_1%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Samuel%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ESaul%20Tries%20to%20Kill%20David%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3ESaul%20now%20urged%20his%20servants%20and%20his%20son%20Jonathan%20to%20assassinate%20David.%20But%20Jonathan%2C%20because%20of%20his%20strong%20affection%20for%20David%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_19_2%2